instNote: ﻿The Benedictine Nuns are enlarging their convent, which, when completed, will afford sufficient room for the many applicants who now desire admittance to the Order. Meanwhile the nuns have simply charge of the female schools of the congregation, until the building, when finished, will also permit them to open a boarding-school
